Project Information
Project Title: Trishia Mae Poultrys Lifecycle Tracker

Developer: Trishia Mae L. Mañabat

Selected Farm Business: Poultry (Chicken/Eggs Production)

Description of System
The Trishia Mae Poultrys system is a blockchain-based traceability solution designed to monitor the lifecycle of poultry products. By utilizing the Ethereum blockchain, the system ensures that every batch of eggs or chicken is tracked from the farm to the distributor with absolute transparency. This prevents data tampering and provides a verified audit trail for food safety and business integrity.

 Contract Features
Product Registration: Allows the authorized farmer to log new batches with unique IDs, pricing, and origin details.

Ownership Tracking: Real-time recording of the current holder of the poultry batch.

Status Updates: A three-stage lifecycle: Created (0), InTransit (1), and Delivered (2).

Automatic Transfer Logic: When a product is transferred, the status is automatically updated to "In Transit" to maintain data accuracy.

Access Control: Secured functions ensure only the "Farmer" can register products, and only the "Current Owner" can move or deliver them.

Data Retrieval: Public functions to view full batch details and the complete ownership audit history.
